circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery: No NOK: 82 year old female, reported skilled nursing facility death due to suspected natural causes. Per the hospice nurse, on 10/31, end of life planning was initiated, however, due to D not having any NOK, the OCME was contacted regarding next steps. Social work was informed of the transitional assistance program and instructed to call back at the time of death if NOK issues persisted. Per social work notes, on 11/13, the healthcare proxy/friend was contacted, but stated due to legal issues she is unable to access D's funds and would not be making funeral arrangements. A follow-up note (11/30), indicates multiple funeral homes were contacted via social work, but none would accept due to the financial issues. The reporting is unable to provide a list of the funeral homes that declined. The healthcare proxy then became uncooperative regarding the situation. D continued to make a steady decline until expiring on 12/07. There are no external signs of trauma observed. There are no recent falls or injuries reported. There are no concerns for abuse, neglect, or foul play. There is nothing suspicious or concerning regarding the death.

circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery:
OCME Case # 2023-897
69 y/o black male suspected death related to a traumatic MVA in 1989. Cremation Flag. D was in an MVA in 1989 in his home state of Virginia. D was a passenger and was a paraplegic after the MVC. D remained alert and oriented and lived in multiple SNFs since. Unclear when D moved to Ma., but he was in a SNF that closed. He moved to his current SNF Southeast Rehab years ago, unclear date. RN Reports D reports D remained alert and oriented but would never talk about the MVA. On 11/28/2022 D was noted to be hypotensive, lethargic, and with fevers. He went to Good Samaritan MC where imaging revealed a hip/gluteal abscess consuming his left thigh with femoral osteomyelitis related to his decubiti ulcers. He was admitted for sepsis and medically managed. Psych did consult and deamed D alert and oriented with allowance to make own decisions. On 12/2/2022 D transitioned himself to CMO. He remained in the hospital but died on 12/9/2022 , Covid19/Flu/RSV negative. RN reports ulcers to his coccyx and extremities as his only trauma. RN confirms no other information on the accident and D was not embalmed at this time.
